      "term": "protandrously",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "null",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "adverb",
          "definition": "in a protandrous manner; describing an organism whose male reproductive organs mature earlier than its female ones",
          "examples": [
            "The flowers open protandrously to reduce self-pollination.",
            "Some species release pollen protandrously before the stigma becomes receptive."
